    "en": {
      "title": "Tusker Bharana found dead mysteriously",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Tusker Bharana, was one of the few remaining giant tuskers in the island and had attracted more tourists in Kalawewa International Park, was found dead mysteriously.",
        "The carcass of the tusker was found in the National Namal Uyana forest reserve in Galkiriagama by the Galkiriyagama wildlife officers, a short while ago.",
        "The wildlife officials suspected that the tusker might have died this morning, but the cause of the death was not revealed.",
        "Preliminary investigations were conducted by the officers of Galkiriagama Wildlife Site Protection Office and Galkiriagama Police Station.",
        "The tusker is nearly 35 years old and possesses a pair of tusks nearly four feet in height.",
        "The tusker often roams near the Kalawewa National Park and the National Namal Uyana regularly. (Kushan Jayawardana)"
      ],
